<header>
<div class="blogparent"><a href="../words" rel="tag">Words</a>:</div>
<h1>I’m Talking to You</h1>
<small>January 6, 2019</small>
</header>

<p>
Hey.<br>
Yeah, <strong>I’m talking to you.</strong><br>
Fine, look around.<br>
But you won’t see me. I’m right here. 
</p><p>
Where have you been?<br>
I’ve been trying to talk to you.<br>
Have you forgotten me?<br>
Have you moved on?
</p><p>
Relationships ebb and flow.<br>
Of this, I know.<br>
If you’re not feeling this anymore, that’s okay.<br>
I’ll still be here waiting.<br>
Until the day you decide our relationship's worth saving.
</p><p>
You’ll be just fine without me.<br>
You’ll be able to make it.<br>
But I truly believe that together we can be so much more.<br>
You just have to be willing to walk through the door.
</p><p>
Relationships are a two-way street.<br>
So I won’t force you into it.<br>
Even if I know it would be a beautiful union.<br>
Even if I know we would have a beautiful communion.<br>
</p><p>
I’m still here.<br>
I haven’t left.<br>
It’s up to you.<br>
Shall we start anew?
</p>

